00:34:30.664 --> 00:34:35.196
the galaxies that are there.
Okay, so now,

00:34:35.196 --> 00:34:45.780
let me show you a simulation.
Let's see. Come on.

00:34:45.780 --> 00:34:48.261
Here we go. All right.
I'll come back and I'll tell

00:34:48.261 --> 00:34:49.789
you what you're looking at in
just a second.

00:34:49.789 --> 00:34:55.070
But here is the evolution of
the Universe as done by

00:34:55.070 --> 00:34:56.908
computer.
All right.

00:34:56.908 --> 00:34:59.980
So now, let me--where are we
starting from?

00:34:59.980 --> 00:35:03.583
The redshift is up here.
And so, we're going to go from

00:35:03.583 --> 00:35:05.900
a redshift of about thirty,
when the Universe was thirty

00:35:05.900 --> 00:35:08.614
times smaller than it is,
to a redshift of zero,

00:35:08.614 --> 00:35:11.056
which is today.
And we're going to look at this

00:35:11.056 --> 00:35:12.534
box.
This is a little chunk of the

00:35:12.534 --> 00:35:14.574
Universe.
Each one of these dots is

00:35:14.574 --> 00:35:17.656
supposed to be a galaxy.
Now, at a redshift of thirty,

00:35:17.656 --> 00:35:20.891
they're not galaxies yet.
They're just over-densities of

00:35:20.891 --> 00:35:22.698
gas.
Now, two things are going to

00:35:22.698 --> 00:35:25.090
happen, since a redshift has
started by now.

00:35:25.090 --> 00:35:27.519
One is that the box is going to
get thirty times bigger.

00:35:27.519 --> 00:35:29.500
The whole Universe is going to
expand.

00:35:29.500 --> 00:35:32.515
And that is included in the
simulation, but we're not going

00:35:32.515 --> 00:35:35.686
to include it when we make the
movie, because it makes it hard

00:35:35.686 --> 00:35:38.999
to see what's going on.
And so, if you'll remember the

00:35:38.999 --> 00:35:41.863
coordinate system,
the way it works is there's

00:35:41.863 --> 00:35:44.536
this scale factor times
x, y,

00:35:44.536 --> 00:35:47.774
z position.
We're taking the scale factor

00:35:47.774 --> 00:35:50.513
out.
So, this box is a single part

00:35:50.513 --> 00:35:52.942
of the Universe.
It's going to expand by a

00:35:52.942 --> 00:35:54.707
factor of 30,
but you're not going to see the

00:35:54.707 --> 00:35:57.296
expansion here.
All you're going to see is the

00:35:57.296 --> 00:36:00.344
motion in x,
y and z, not the

00:36:00.344 --> 00:36:02.894
scale factor,
as these things moved toward

00:36:02.894 --> 00:36:05.203
each other.
Now, as you start out,

00:36:05.203 --> 00:36:07.829
it looks like it's pretty
evenly distributed,

00:36:07.829 --> 00:36:10.396
but, in fact,
there are little perturbations

00:36:10.396 --> 00:36:13.024
in the density.
And what will happen is the

00:36:13.024 --> 00:36:15.786
galaxies will stream toward the
perturbations and the

00:36:15.786 --> 00:36:19.725
perturbations will get bigger.
And the--keep track of redshift

00:36:19.725 --> 00:36:21.971
up here.
The rate at which the redshift

00:36:21.971 --> 00:36:24.819
changes, varies with time,
because what we're actually

00:36:24.819 --> 00:36:26.485
counting, here,
is not redshift,

00:36:26.485 --> 00:36:29.212
but time steps.
And the relationship between

00:36:29.212 --> 00:36:31.219
time and redshift is not
obvious.

00:36:31.219 --> 00:36:35.673
So, let us take another look at
the growth of structure,

00:36:35.673 --> 00:36:38.687
here.
See them all moving towards

00:36:38.687 --> 00:36:43.945
each other, collecting in these
filaments, abandoning whole

00:36:43.945 --> 00:36:47.612
regions into voids.
And then, you end up--well,

00:36:47.612 --> 00:36:51.082
you end up back where you
started, the way this film loop

00:36:51.082 --> 00:36:53.364
works.
But let me show you a different

00:36:53.364 --> 00:36:55.590
visualization of exactly the
same data.

00:36:55.590 --> 00:36:56.660
You know, this is all on the
computer.

00:36:56.660 --> 00:36:58.937
You can do anything you want.
They make these great things

00:36:58.937 --> 00:37:01.437
where you sort of fly through
the Universe while it's evolving

00:37:01.437 --> 00:37:03.237
and stuff.
I don't think--That's amusing,

00:37:03.237 --> 00:37:04.969
but I don't think it's very
educational.

00:37:04.969 --> 00:37:08.057
One thing that is useful:
they took that box and they

00:37:08.057 --> 00:37:11.619
just kept rotating it as this
